  "prompt": "What is the purpose of compression shorts?",
  "response": "Compression shorts are a type of clothing typically worn by athletes during physical activity. They serve several purposes:\n\n1. **Muscle Support**: Compression shorts help to stabilize muscles during movement, reducing muscle oscillation and fatigue. This can enhance performance and reduce the risk of injury.\n\n2. **Improved Circulation**: By applying pressure to the muscles, compression shorts can promote blood flow, which helps to deliver oxygen and nutrients to the muscles more efficiently. This can speed up recovery times after exercise.\n\n3. **Temperature Regulation**: The snug fit of compression shorts can help to keep the muscles warm, which can be beneficial in colder conditions. They can also wick away sweat, helping to keep the body cool in warmer conditions.\n\n4. **Comfort and Fit**: Compression shorts often provide a comfortable, secure fit that can be worn under other clothing. They can reduce chafing and skin irritation during physical activity.\n\n5. **Body Shaping**: Some people wear compression shorts for aesthetic reasons, as they can help to smooth out the appearance of the body and enhance the silhouette.\n\nOverall, compression shorts are designed to enhance performance, comfort, and recovery during physical activity.",
